# Net Change Limit of 300 Million ADA for Epochs 613 – 713

## 📊 Title: **Net Change Limit of 300 Million ADA for Epochs 613 – 713**

**Governance Action Type:** Info Action (sentiment signal)

**Submitted:** Feb 6, 2026 (Epoch 611)

**Voting Window:** Covers Epochs 613 – 713

**Status:** Live voting for stakeholder signals on this limit.

**TLDR:** The Net Change Limit (NCL) sets the maximum ADA that can be withdrawn from the Cardano treasury in a given period and is typically aligned with the treasury’s annual inflows (~315 M ADA, ±15%) to maintain sustainability, but because a new NCL has not yet been agreed upon, the broader budgeting process has been stalled since December.

---

## 📌 Summary (What the Proposal Is)

This governance action proposes setting a **Net Change Limit** of **300 million ADA** (as lovelace) for the specified period (Epochs 613–713). Essentially, it’s a parameter used in Cardano’s governance and treasury processes that ***caps aggregate changes to treasury spending and withdrawals within a timeframe*** — helping ensure fiscal discipline and predictable budgeting. As an ***Info Action*,** this proposal doesn’t itself enact a change but allows Delegated Representatives (DReps) and voters to indicate whether they support this parameter signal.

> *Net Change Limits* are governance parameters tied to the protocol’s economic controls. They help define how much liquidity or allocation may be shifted via governance actions within an epoch range. This type of parameter can affect how treasury budgeting, withdrawals, and resource allocations get approved or executed.
> 

